"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-olympics-laura-collett-eventing-dujardin-paris-b2587798.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Eventing delivered the first Team GB gold of the Olympics, with Laura Collett delighted to bring positivity after the Charlotte Dujardin  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999987712570149, \"rank\": 1.228752027816938e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Much of Versaille's gilded grandeur was made during the 1789 French Revolution but it was Great Britain who snatched the gold from under French noses at theirOlympics.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\", \"score\": 0.9991892796715697, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Versaille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9843529457292766, \"rank\": 0.014602948759760101, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9666693051593038, \"rank\": 0.023478269463349664, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura Collett praised her prince of a horse as he delivered another Olympic team title - and individual bronze - in the garden of France's famous Sun King atParis 2024.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Louis XIV's palace seems the fitting venue forTeam GBto make the top of the podium for the first time in Paris, meaning they remain the only nation that has won a gold medal at every Olympics dating back to 1896.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"score\": 0.999999999911779, \"rank\": 8.828673453199653e-11, \"text\": \"Louis XIV\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.27665065290092e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Collett and Tom McEwen won team gold three years ago in Tokyo and joined forces with Ros Canter to defend their title, as hosts France and Japan completed the podium.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"score\": 0.8873196584612367, \"rank\": 0.07814407814405706, \"text\": \"Tom McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999080388761163, \"rank\": 9.196585697180506e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1165, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9453098228038023, \"rank\": 0.037900953708945175, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then Collett came back to ride her second flawless round on London 52 - who she nicknames Dan - to claim individual bronze.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999900001058, \"rank\": 4.9565273214335144e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted to have been sat on a nervous horse but thankfully he rose to the occasion,\\\" said Collett.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He loves showing off and he thinks he's right at home with the palace in the background and everyone watching him.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's waited three years for a full stadium.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The noise was unreal, but it did not distract him at all.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's a true professional and I think he knew what was at stake.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1719, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would not wanted to have sat on any other horse.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew coming here we stood a good chance because the horsepower Team GB has at the moment is second to none, we could have fielded another team with the reserves as they could have won a gold medal.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999987712570149, \"rank\": 1.228752027816938e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's quite a strange feeling winning two medals, I had about five minutes to enjoy that team gold, two Olympic medals is something I'd never even dream about.\\\"\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been a difficult few days for the British equestrian team in Paris, following the suspension of six-time Olympic dressage medallist Charlotte Dujardin, after footage emerged of her repeatedly whipping a horse in training.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.27665065290092e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Collett insists the team's performance would not be possible if horses were mistreated.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's huge for our sport for people to see our horses go out there and look a million dollars,\\\" she added,  \\\"There is a huge team behind us that make it possible, and horses do not perform like that if they are not happy.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our job was to focus on our horses and show the world that they are the real stars of the show, we are just the ones that get to enjoy these moments on them.\\\"\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain had a slender five-point advantage heading into the decisive jumping after Canter picked up just four penalties and McEwen went clear, meaning Collett had the luxury of knowing she could knock down four fences and still win.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9243136312589222, \"rank\": 0.08185892512907553, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2966, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.995493243301195e-15, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's final rider whipped up the crowd as Collett entered the area, the Entente Cordiale creaking, but Collett and London 52 were nerveless under the most intense pressure.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999900001058, \"rank\": 4.9565273214335144e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wasn't that nervous watching her,\\\" said McEwen \\\"She jumped amazingly, I thought I would be more nervous, I much prefer doing it myself to be honest.\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3296, \"end\": 3302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.995493243301195e-15, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it was a class round from Laura, and it was poetry in motion.\", \"from\": 3406, \"to\": 3472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3437, \"end\": 3442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"score\": 0.9922182229177872, \"rank\": 0.007839735856933755, \"text\": \"Laura\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/X-23\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We came here for team gold and that's what we are walking away.\\\"\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Collett and McEwen could also add to their medal haul in the individual event later today, sitting third and fourth in those standings.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.995493243301195e-15, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These equestrians are made of tough stuff, Collett spent seven days in coma 11 years ago after a fall which left her blind in her right eye.\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3749, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coma\", \"score\": 0.999999997591658, \"rank\": 2.4053217441614923e-09, \"text\": \"coma\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wears special googles in bright sunlight, which she certainly needed as temperatures reached 34 degrees in Versaille.\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3941, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3931, \"end\": 3940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\", \"score\": 0.9991892796715697, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Versaille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Versailles,_Yvelines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She describes London 52 as her horse of a lifetime, though he was outside her budget when first spotted in Germany.\", \"from\": 3943, \"to\": 4058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3957, \"end\": 3963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999900001058, \"rank\": 4.9565273214335144e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 4050, \"end\": 4057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.6708712335969078, \"rank\": 0.4424768704560585, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, she clubbed together with co-owners Karen Bartlett and Keith Scott, training the horse at her base in the Cotswolds.\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4104, \"end\": 4109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\", \"score\": 0.9518416732644558, \"rank\": 0.041848982136056895, \"text\": \"Karen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Carpenter\"}, {\"begin\": 4123, \"end\": 4134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\", \"score\": 0.5297979123518304, \"rank\": 0.7754100477849662, \"text\": \"Keith Scott\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keith_Scott_(voice_actor)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He's never been the bravest horse,\\\" added Collett.\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When he was a young horse, it was about building a partnership, so he trusted what I was asking him.\", \"from\": 4238, \"to\": 4339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I first saw him he was very sassy but something about him caught my eye.\", \"from\": 4341, \"to\": 4419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took some time for him to have belief in himself.\\\"\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aldi are proud Official Partners of Team GB & ParalympicsGB, supporting all athletes through toParis 2024  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 4475, \"to\": 4812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4475, \"end\": 4479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aldi\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aldi\"}, {\"begin\": 4633, \"end\": 4644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.353642853137286e-18, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"